# Keep operator state out of the image. The Dockerfile does `COPY agent/ ./agent/`, which does NOT
# read .gitignore — without this file the image ships the builder's private data: the Fernet key that
# protects encrypted learnings, chroma vectors derived from real conversations, governance logs, and
# runtime_config.json full of local machine paths.
#
# This only matters when someone builds and SHARES an image or tarball; a friend building from their
# own clean clone was never affected. It is still the same class of leak as the installer, so it gets
# the same treatment.

# ── Operator state directories ──
**/.layla/
**/.governance/
.governance/
**/chroma_db/
**/.research_lab/
**/.research_brain/
**/.identity/

# ── Operator data files ──
*.db
*.db-wal
*.db-shm
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3
*.graphml
*.graphml.bak
**/knowledge_graph.graphml*
agent/runtime_config.json
runtime_config.json
agent/titles.txt
conversation_history.json
**/project_memory.json
**/memory_encryption.key
**/repo_index.db
benchmarks/scorecard_live.json
learnings.json

# ── Build/dev noise ──
.git/
.venv/
.venv-test/
**/__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
.pytest_cache/
node_modules/
dist/
build/
*.egg-info/
installer/payload/
installer/output/
logs/
models/
*.gguf
.planning/
